1
00:00:05,333 --> 00:00:07,266
[theme song]

2
00:01:53,115 --> 00:01:56,048
-Ichi-- oof!

3
00:01:56,082 --> 00:01:59,448
-What's up, Keigo?

4
00:01:59,482 --> 00:02:00,282
-But why?

5
00:02:00,315 --> 00:02:03,682
I didn't even say anything yet!

6
00:02:03,715 --> 00:02:05,348
-Hey, Mizuiro.

7
00:02:05,382 --> 00:02:06,415
-Oh, hey, Ichigo.

8
00:02:06,448 --> 00:02:07,782
Quiet morning, isn't it?

9
00:02:07,815 --> 00:02:09,348
-Yep, sure is.

10
00:02:09,382 --> 00:02:10,115
-Stop!

11
00:02:10,148 --> 00:02:11,782
Didn't you just see that?

12
00:02:11,815 --> 00:02:13,248
He just smashed my face!

13
00:02:13,282 --> 00:02:15,782
Why are you pretending
like I don't exist?

14
00:02:15,815 --> 00:02:16,882
-Oh, yeah.

15
00:02:16,915 --> 00:02:18,015
There was someone here
to see you earlier.

16
00:02:18,048 --> 00:02:18,982
-To see me?

17
00:02:23,715 --> 00:02:24,615
-Hm?

18
00:02:24,648 --> 00:02:25,448
-Hm?

19
00:02:25,482 --> 00:02:26,348
-Mm.

20
00:02:26,382 --> 00:02:26,848
-Hm.

21
00:02:30,682 --> 00:02:33,548
-Long time no see, Ichigo.

22
00:02:33,582 --> 00:02:35,182
[laughing]

23
00:02:39,415 --> 00:02:42,548
-As always, everyone
is so carefree here.

24
00:02:42,582 --> 00:02:45,682
No one even scolds you
for playing Kemari.

25
00:02:45,715 --> 00:02:48,915
It's sure a far cry
from life at the palace.

26
00:02:48,948 --> 00:02:51,948
I do envy you.

27
00:02:51,982 --> 00:02:52,715
-So what's up?

28
00:02:52,748 --> 00:02:54,648
Is something going on?

29
00:02:54,682 --> 00:02:55,682
-Hm?

30
00:02:55,715 --> 00:02:57,815
-I mean, why'd you
bother coming back here?

31
00:02:57,848 --> 00:02:59,048
And all alone, too?

32
00:02:59,082 --> 00:03:01,848
-I may travel
wherever I so please.

33
00:03:01,882 --> 00:03:03,815
And besides, if
anything bad happens,

34
00:03:03,848 --> 00:03:05,648
I am sure you will protect me.

35
00:03:05,682 --> 00:03:06,915
-That's quite an assumption.

36
00:03:06,948 --> 00:03:10,048
You know, I've got my own
things to take care of as well.

37
00:03:10,082 --> 00:03:11,748
Where are Kenryu and Enryu?

38
00:03:11,782 --> 00:03:13,782
Aren't they around somewhere?

39
00:03:13,815 --> 00:03:15,382
-I have no idea.

40
00:03:15,415 --> 00:03:17,748
I came here all by myself.

41
00:03:17,782 --> 00:03:19,015
-Huh?

42
00:03:19,048 --> 00:03:20,548
Hold on.

43
00:03:20,582 --> 00:03:23,448
But aren't you the head
of the Kasumioji clan now?

44
00:03:23,482 --> 00:03:24,915
Isn't that a little dangerous?

45
00:03:24,948 --> 00:03:26,782
-I'm well aware of the dangers.

46
00:03:26,815 --> 00:03:28,548
Listen, I have a
good reason why--

47
00:03:28,582 --> 00:03:29,682
-Hold that thought.

48
00:03:29,715 --> 00:03:30,982
I got a class to get to.

49
00:03:31,015 --> 00:03:31,482
-Wait!

50
00:03:31,515 --> 00:03:32,115
No!

51
00:03:32,148 --> 00:03:35,315
Come back at once!

52
00:03:35,348 --> 00:03:37,148
-What did you hit me for?

53
00:03:37,182 --> 00:03:39,448
-Listen to what I have to say!

54
00:03:43,215 --> 00:03:44,615
-Maybe you should calm down.

55
00:03:49,882 --> 00:03:54,315
-[growling] Ichigo, you jerk!

56
00:03:59,815 --> 00:04:01,182
-Yes!

57
00:04:01,215 --> 00:04:03,115
It's lunch time!

58
00:04:03,148 --> 00:04:06,948
Well, Ichigo, what do you
think today's main course is

59
00:04:06,982 --> 00:04:08,082
gonna be?

60
00:04:08,115 --> 00:04:09,415
-If you're looking for
Ichigo, he left already.

61
00:04:09,448 --> 00:04:10,215
-Huh?

62
00:04:10,248 --> 00:04:11,115
That fast?

63
00:04:11,148 --> 00:04:12,315
No way!

64
00:04:12,348 --> 00:04:15,348
He's taken blowing me
off to a whole new level.

65
00:04:15,382 --> 00:04:16,815
-By herself?

66
00:04:16,848 --> 00:04:17,882
-That's right.

67
00:04:17,915 --> 00:04:20,215
She doesn't have Kenryu
or Enryu with her.

68
00:04:20,248 --> 00:04:22,948
-Do you have any idea
why she came back?

69
00:04:22,982 --> 00:04:24,282
-I don't know.

70
00:04:24,315 --> 00:04:26,315
Maybe she just got sick of
living at that palace of hers

71
00:04:26,348 --> 00:04:28,082
and decided to run away.

72
00:04:28,115 --> 00:04:28,848
-I see.

73
00:04:28,882 --> 00:04:31,448
And where's Rurichiyo now?

74
00:04:31,482 --> 00:04:34,448
-Beats me.

75
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:35,682
That really hurt!

76
00:04:35,715 --> 00:04:36,782
-Idiot!

77
00:04:36,815 --> 00:04:38,282
Even though her clan
isn't fighting anymore,

78
00:04:38,315 --> 00:04:39,882
she's still a princess!

79
00:04:39,915 --> 00:04:42,948
What if something
happens to her here?

80
00:04:42,982 --> 00:04:44,948
-What could happen to her?

81
00:04:49,015 --> 00:04:49,515
-Innertube!

82
00:04:49,548 --> 00:04:50,548
I've got it!

83
00:04:50,582 --> 00:04:52,748
What we need is a life jacket!

84
00:04:52,782 --> 00:04:55,282
-And how on earth did you
come to the conclusion

85
00:04:55,315 --> 00:04:57,348
that we need a life jacket?

86
00:04:57,382 --> 00:04:58,682
-It's simple.

87
00:04:58,715 --> 00:05:01,148
Rurichiyo has jumped
from the pier of despair

88
00:05:01,182 --> 00:05:03,015
into the ocean of sorrow.

89
00:05:03,048 --> 00:05:04,082
She'll drown in a sea of--

90
00:05:04,115 --> 00:05:04,982
-Orihime.

91
00:05:05,015 --> 00:05:06,282
-Huh?

92
00:05:06,315 --> 00:05:08,782
-This sounds like it's gonna
take too long to explain.

93
00:05:08,815 --> 00:05:10,148
-OK.

94
00:05:10,182 --> 00:05:12,315
-Let's split up and find her
before anything bad happens.

95
00:05:12,348 --> 00:05:15,015
-Right.

96
00:05:15,048 --> 00:05:16,115
-Guess I have no choice.

97
00:05:38,215 --> 00:05:39,348
-Find her?

98
00:05:39,382 --> 00:05:40,848
-Uh-uh.

99
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:42,048
-Oh, man.

100
00:05:42,082 --> 00:05:43,715
Even though she's
head of her clan now,

101
00:05:43,748 --> 00:05:46,615
she still loves causing
trouble, doesn't she?

102
00:05:46,648 --> 00:05:47,848
-That's true.

103
00:05:47,882 --> 00:05:54,282
But remember, even though
she's head of her clan,

104
00:05:54,315 --> 00:05:56,115
she's still just a child.

105
00:05:56,148 --> 00:06:00,448
We have no idea how heavy
a burden that must be.

106
00:06:00,482 --> 00:06:04,348
It drove her to seek refuge
in the world of the living.

107
00:06:04,382 --> 00:06:06,515
We can't waste any more time.

108
00:06:06,548 --> 00:06:08,748
Let's keep looking for her.

109
00:06:08,782 --> 00:06:09,382
-Right.

110
00:06:09,415 --> 00:06:10,548
-What's going on?

111
00:06:10,582 --> 00:06:12,182
-Huh?

112
00:06:12,215 --> 00:06:13,282
-Uryu.

113
00:06:13,315 --> 00:06:14,615
-Uryu!

114
00:06:14,648 --> 00:06:15,948
Rurichiyo has gone missing.

115
00:06:15,982 --> 00:06:18,448
Any idea where she might be?

116
00:06:18,482 --> 00:06:19,115
-Well, actually.

117
00:06:23,148 --> 00:06:25,515
-My, my, my, my.

118
00:06:25,548 --> 00:06:29,648
I was wondering when you'd swing
on by to pick her up, Ichigo.

119
00:06:29,682 --> 00:06:31,715
I assumed you'd come
here right away,

120
00:06:31,748 --> 00:06:33,682
so I didn't bother
contacting you.

121
00:06:33,715 --> 00:06:36,115
What took you guys so long?

122
00:06:36,148 --> 00:06:37,482
-Well, I, uh--

123
00:06:37,515 --> 00:06:39,482
-Yeah, we were just--

124
00:06:39,515 --> 00:06:44,348
-So why didn't you think
of checking here earlier?

125
00:06:44,382 --> 00:06:45,615
-Anyway, let's go.

126
00:06:45,648 --> 00:06:46,582
-No!

127
00:06:46,615 --> 00:06:48,248
I will be staying here.

128
00:06:48,282 --> 00:06:51,415
Do not make me go with that
strange orange haired man!

129
00:06:51,448 --> 00:06:52,448
-Really?

130
00:06:52,482 --> 00:06:54,448
You're still using
that old insult on me?

131
00:06:54,482 --> 00:06:56,648
Listen, if you won't
cooperate, I'm gonna--

132
00:06:56,682 --> 00:06:59,315
-I'm telling you
to leave me alone.

133
00:06:59,348 --> 00:07:01,248
-Oh come on, I can't do that.

134
00:07:01,282 --> 00:07:02,515
-And why not?

135
00:07:02,548 --> 00:07:04,515
-Because when you just
show up like this,

136
00:07:04,548 --> 00:07:07,048
it causes everyone
here a lot of problems.

137
00:07:07,082 --> 00:07:09,348
You're in charge of
a noble clan now!

138
00:07:09,382 --> 00:07:10,748
-Fine!

139
00:07:10,782 --> 00:07:12,882
I am a selfish, spoiled noble
who knows nothing of the world!

140
00:07:12,915 --> 00:07:14,148
-Whoa, what's gotten into you?

141
00:07:14,182 --> 00:07:14,848
-Silence!

142
00:07:14,882 --> 00:07:16,915
I do not need you to--

143
00:07:16,948 --> 00:07:18,315
[stomach growls]

144
00:07:18,348 --> 00:07:20,182
-Huh?

145
00:07:20,215 --> 00:07:22,848
You're in a bad mood
because you're hungry.

146
00:07:22,882 --> 00:07:23,415
-No!

147
00:07:23,448 --> 00:07:24,248
That was not me!

148
00:07:24,282 --> 00:07:26,182
I assure you, I am not hungry!

149
00:07:26,215 --> 00:07:28,082
-Sorry.

150
00:07:28,115 --> 00:07:29,848
You heard all that?

151
00:07:29,882 --> 00:07:32,215
URYU (VOICEOVER):
So it was Orihime?

152
00:07:32,248 --> 00:07:34,248
CHAD (VOICEOVER): What
incredible timing.

153
00:07:34,282 --> 00:07:36,515
-Obviously I'm hungry.

154
00:07:36,548 --> 00:07:38,415
You want to go eat something?

155
00:07:38,448 --> 00:07:39,348
[stomach growls]

156
00:07:39,382 --> 00:07:40,782
-Huh?

157
00:07:40,815 --> 00:07:44,582
-Uh, oh, excuse me.

158
00:07:44,615 --> 00:07:45,848
That one was me.

159
00:07:51,248 --> 00:07:53,948
-That was delicious.

160
00:07:53,982 --> 00:07:57,148
Only in this world can you get
exquisite meals like that one.

161
00:07:57,182 --> 00:07:59,682
Where is my after dinner tea?

162
00:07:59,715 --> 00:08:02,415
You there, waiter,
fetch me my tea!

163
00:08:02,448 --> 00:08:04,848
-Um, Rurichiyo, you
don't have to yell.

164
00:08:13,948 --> 00:08:15,882
-[yawn]

165
00:08:28,248 --> 00:08:30,315
-The princess is sound asleep.

166
00:08:30,348 --> 00:08:32,548
-If only she were this
quiet when she's awake,

167
00:08:32,582 --> 00:08:33,882
I'd be a happy man.

168
00:08:33,915 --> 00:08:35,982
-Sorry for being so loud.

169
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:38,282
-Uh, did you hear all that?

170
00:08:38,315 --> 00:08:41,848
Well, anyway, things must
be pretty rough for you

171
00:08:41,882 --> 00:08:42,848
these days.

172
00:08:42,882 --> 00:08:46,782
-I do not need your sympathy.

173
00:08:46,815 --> 00:08:49,015
-Well, sorry for
leaving you like that.

174
00:08:49,048 --> 00:08:50,448
-Huh?

175
00:08:50,482 --> 00:08:50,948
Hm.

176
00:08:57,748 --> 00:08:59,182
Huh?

177
00:08:59,215 --> 00:08:59,882
Who's there?

178
00:09:02,482 --> 00:09:04,848
-Kenryu?

179
00:09:04,882 --> 00:09:06,982
-Lady Rurichiyo,
leaving the clan

180
00:09:07,015 --> 00:09:09,948
and coming to the world of
the living is outrageous.

181
00:09:09,982 --> 00:09:11,648
What could you
have been thinking?

182
00:09:11,682 --> 00:09:13,215
-Hey, hang on a minute!

183
00:09:13,248 --> 00:09:14,848
Give her a chance to explain.

184
00:09:14,882 --> 00:09:16,815
-I know I scolded you
about playing kemari,

185
00:09:16,848 --> 00:09:19,415
but was this really an
appropriate response?

186
00:09:19,448 --> 00:09:21,115
-No, that's not why she came.

187
00:09:21,148 --> 00:09:21,682
She wouldn't--

188
00:09:21,715 --> 00:09:22,382
-I would!

189
00:09:25,448 --> 00:09:27,848
What is so wicked about kemari?

190
00:09:27,882 --> 00:09:31,282
-As I said, we have a
mountain of critical matters

191
00:09:31,315 --> 00:09:33,448
to handle before we
run off playing kemari!

192
00:09:33,482 --> 00:09:35,948
-As your ruler, that
is for me to decide.

193
00:09:35,982 --> 00:09:36,948
-Hold on a sec!

194
00:09:36,982 --> 00:09:40,048
The reason you came here was--

195
00:09:40,082 --> 00:09:40,548
-Kemari!

196
00:09:44,315 --> 00:09:46,215
-That is what I
keep telling you!

197
00:09:46,248 --> 00:09:49,515
Right now, a fun distraction
like kemari is important.

198
00:09:49,548 --> 00:09:52,182
-I have already gone over
this with you again and again,

199
00:09:52,215 --> 00:09:53,948
but you refuse to understand.

200
00:09:53,982 --> 00:09:56,348
With your subjects feeling
alienated from you,

201
00:09:56,382 --> 00:09:58,148
our priority is
repairing relations

202
00:09:58,182 --> 00:09:59,882
with the other noble leaders.

203
00:09:59,915 --> 00:10:01,815
-I do not know
about such things.

204
00:10:01,848 --> 00:10:05,115
But I am in command now,
and I will do as I see fit.

205
00:10:05,148 --> 00:10:06,915
-That is unacceptable!

206
00:10:06,948 --> 00:10:08,582
-Just hang on a minute.

207
00:10:08,615 --> 00:10:10,015
Both of you need to calm down.

208
00:10:10,048 --> 00:10:12,882
-How do you expect
me to calm down?

209
00:10:12,915 --> 00:10:14,748
Ichigo, you talk
some sense into him.

210
00:10:14,782 --> 00:10:16,415
-You see what I deal with?

211
00:10:16,448 --> 00:10:19,182
You're on my side here,
aren't you, Ichigo?

212
00:10:19,215 --> 00:10:21,448
-Come on, Ichigo, do something!

213
00:10:21,482 --> 00:10:23,548
-Ichigo Kurosaki!

214
00:10:23,582 --> 00:10:24,848
-Oh, come on.

215
00:10:24,882 --> 00:10:26,748
Just leave me out of this.

216
00:10:26,782 --> 00:10:29,182
-[growling]

217
00:10:29,215 --> 00:10:30,948
-[growling]

218
00:10:30,982 --> 00:10:32,182
Hmph.

219
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:34,248
Are you telling me that you
will forbid what I want,

220
00:10:34,282 --> 00:10:35,548
no matter how much I insist?

221
00:10:35,582 --> 00:10:37,548
Is that it?

222
00:10:37,582 --> 00:10:38,682
-That's right.

223
00:10:38,715 --> 00:10:40,648
Milady, I'm aware that I
have very little chance

224
00:10:40,682 --> 00:10:44,315
of persuading that
stubborn head of yours.

225
00:10:44,348 --> 00:10:45,148
-Stubborn?

226
00:10:45,182 --> 00:10:47,515
-But it is my duty nonetheless.

227
00:10:47,548 --> 00:10:49,715
My resolve will not
falter, even if it

228
00:10:49,748 --> 00:10:52,648
means I will incur my
lady's wrathful anger.

229
00:10:52,682 --> 00:10:54,315
-I never liked you, Kenryu!

230
00:10:54,348 --> 00:10:56,982
Why, in fact, I hate you!

231
00:11:02,382 --> 00:11:05,082
I've hated you since
I first met you!

232
00:11:05,115 --> 00:11:08,848
If you refuse to obey
me, then leave my sight!

233
00:11:14,115 --> 00:11:15,282
-Very well then.

234
00:11:18,948 --> 00:11:20,815
Excuse me.

235
00:11:20,848 --> 00:11:23,315
-Sir Kenryu?

236
00:11:23,348 --> 00:11:25,148
-Hey, wait.

237
00:11:25,182 --> 00:11:27,748
Hold on, come back.

238
00:11:27,782 --> 00:11:28,648
Rurichiyo!

239
00:11:28,682 --> 00:11:29,415
-I don't care.

240
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:44,107
-What?

241
00:11:44,140 --> 00:11:45,174
-Yeah.

242
00:11:45,207 --> 00:11:47,874
And now it's Kenryu
who's gone missing.

243
00:11:47,907 --> 00:11:50,140
-That Kasumioji
clan really seems

244
00:11:50,174 --> 00:11:53,507
to enjoy causing a
commotion, don't they?

245
00:11:53,540 --> 00:11:56,340
-But Princess
Rurichiyo-- I mean,

246
00:11:56,374 --> 00:11:58,740
he didn't seem that much
different from her usual self.

247
00:12:04,740 --> 00:12:05,874
-Yeah, you got it!

248
00:12:05,907 --> 00:12:06,707
[interposing voices]

249
00:12:13,207 --> 00:12:15,874
-They are not very skilled.

250
00:12:15,907 --> 00:12:17,240
-Found you!

251
00:12:17,274 --> 00:12:18,374
-Huh?

252
00:12:18,407 --> 00:12:22,074
-What the hell are you
doing out here anyway?

253
00:12:22,107 --> 00:12:23,140
-Oh.

254
00:12:23,174 --> 00:12:24,540
-Sorry, pal.

255
00:12:24,574 --> 00:12:27,307
-Oh, man, that really hurt.

256
00:12:27,340 --> 00:12:27,807
Huh?

257
00:12:36,874 --> 00:12:37,674
[interposing voices]

258
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:46,740
-Did you see that?

259
00:12:46,774 --> 00:12:48,307
My technique is perfect.

260
00:12:48,340 --> 00:12:49,840
-Sure is.

261
00:12:49,874 --> 00:12:50,707
I mean, no!

262
00:12:50,740 --> 00:12:51,774
It's-- wait!

263
00:12:51,807 --> 00:12:54,440
I mean, this isn't
going to solve anything!

264
00:12:54,474 --> 00:13:01,374
--[sigh] Kumoi's incident
is at the root of all this.

