my people lose their
spirit, and ultimately, I

269
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:15,574
am the one responsible.

270
00:13:15,607 --> 00:13:20,074
That is why I had the idea
to hold a kemari festival.

271
00:13:20,107 --> 00:13:22,340
I recalled seeing a similar
event when I was last

272
00:13:22,374 --> 00:13:25,407
in your world, and
I thought perhaps

273
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:28,474
it would make the
people happy again.

274
00:13:28,507 --> 00:13:32,107
So along with Shu,
I worked out a plan.

275
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:33,207
But--

276
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,174
-What are you saying,
Lady Rurichiyo?

277
00:13:35,207 --> 00:13:39,007
Leave this nonsense
alone, for your own good.

278
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:41,040
And for the good of
the Kasumioji clan.

279
00:13:41,074 --> 00:13:42,940
-I am the head of this clan.

280
00:13:42,974 --> 00:13:44,340
Let me lead as I wish to.

281
00:13:44,374 --> 00:13:46,007
-Absolutely not.

282
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:49,340
And I will repeat my
position until it sinks in.

283
00:13:49,374 --> 00:13:52,707
-[growling]

284
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:55,107
RURICHIYO (VOICEOVER): I tried
to explain my plan to him,

285
00:13:55,140 --> 00:13:57,974
but Kenryu would not
even listen to my ideas.

286
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,474
I still believe
the head of a clan

287
00:14:02,507 --> 00:14:05,207
should do what she thinks is
right, even if it is unpopular.

288
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,774
But it has been difficult.

289
00:14:13,307 --> 00:14:16,840
-So it turns out Rurichiyo does
have some pretty good reasons.

290
00:14:16,874 --> 00:14:18,507
But if we go and
explain it to Kenryu,

291
00:14:18,540 --> 00:14:20,540
do you think you'll hear us out?

292
00:14:20,574 --> 00:14:22,340
-Well, I don't know.

293
00:14:22,374 --> 00:14:24,107
The way he reacted
back there, it

294
00:14:24,140 --> 00:14:26,940
would be tough to get him
to even listen to you.

295
00:14:26,974 --> 00:14:28,907
-And no one's going
to explain anything

296
00:14:28,940 --> 00:14:32,040
to him unless we can figure
out where Kenryu went.

297
00:14:32,074 --> 00:14:34,340
-Yeah, you got that right.

298
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:36,007
Where in the world could he be?

299
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:36,507
-Ichigo.

300
00:14:36,540 --> 00:14:37,007
-Huh?

301
00:14:41,707 --> 00:14:42,607
-Wha?

302
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:43,807
-Huh?

303
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:46,540
-Hey, guys.

304
00:14:46,574 --> 00:14:47,640
-I see.

305
00:14:47,674 --> 00:14:50,007
So that was Lady
Rurichiyo's goal.

306
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,240
-That's right.

307
00:14:51,274 --> 00:14:53,574
And the truth is,
Kenryu, she didn't really

308
00:14:53,607 --> 00:14:56,107
mean it when she told
you to take a hike.

309
00:14:56,140 --> 00:14:59,407
So you think you can accept
what she's trying to do?

310
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,340
-It's difficult.

311
00:15:01,374 --> 00:15:05,707
At the moment, Lady Rurichiyo
is solely focused on her people.

312
00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:08,107
And it is true that
regaining their trust

313
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:11,440
and rebuilding the
clan is important.

314
00:15:11,474 --> 00:15:15,640
However, I believe that in order
to restore the Kasumioji clan,

315
00:15:15,674 --> 00:15:18,740
we first need to mend relations
with other noble families

316
00:15:18,774 --> 00:15:23,674
and powerful persons and work
in concert with them to govern.

317
00:15:23,707 --> 00:15:26,407
It's a matter of priorities.

318
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:29,074
One day we can live
Lady Rurichiyo's vision,

319
00:15:29,107 --> 00:15:32,640
but at present, we do
not have that luxury.

320
00:15:32,674 --> 00:15:34,340
Unfortunately, we
must do what we

321
00:15:34,374 --> 00:15:38,074
must do, for above all,
that is best for the people.

322
00:15:38,107 --> 00:15:41,140
-Oh, man, how complicated.

323
00:15:41,174 --> 00:15:44,607
I mean, it sounds like both
of them have valid opinions.

324
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:46,640
What are we supposed to do?

325
00:15:46,674 --> 00:15:48,074
-Hey, don't look at me.

326
00:15:48,107 --> 00:15:49,940
-[sigh]

327
00:15:49,974 --> 00:15:50,874
-Hm.

328
00:15:50,907 --> 00:15:53,674
-This is a conundrum.

329
00:15:53,707 --> 00:15:56,307
-It's all my fault Lady
Rurichiyo feels this way.

330
00:15:56,340 --> 00:16:00,007
I should have
convinced her by now!

331
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:04,307
-What the hell are you doing?

332
00:16:04,340 --> 00:16:08,207
-Since I have failed,
I will offer my life.

333
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,007
-Augh!

334
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:11,207
Wait a minute, wait a minute!

335
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:13,707
-Do not stop me,
Ichigo Kurosaki!

336
00:16:13,740 --> 00:16:16,007
I must bear the responsibility!

337
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:16,707
-Forget that!

338
00:16:16,740 --> 00:16:17,740
Just calm down!

339
00:16:17,774 --> 00:16:19,040
You don't have to
do anything rash!

340
00:16:19,074 --> 00:16:20,207
-Let me do it!

341
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,640
I said stop it!

342
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:26,240
-Wait, Ichigo.

343
00:16:26,274 --> 00:16:27,907
Let him do it.

344
00:16:27,940 --> 00:16:28,874
-What?

345
00:16:28,907 --> 00:16:30,007
Uryu!

346
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:32,074
-Do not dishonor this warrior.

347
00:16:32,107 --> 00:16:33,840
We'll watch him end
his life and report

348
00:16:33,874 --> 00:16:35,374
the news to the princess.

349
00:16:35,407 --> 00:16:36,307
-What?

350
00:16:36,340 --> 00:16:38,474
Wait, what are you saying?

351
00:16:38,507 --> 00:16:40,940
-Kenryu, please proceed
with your ritual.

352
00:16:40,974 --> 00:16:43,840
In fact, I will assist
you if you wish.

353
00:16:43,874 --> 00:16:46,540
Except I'll be using
an arrow rather than

354
00:16:46,574 --> 00:16:47,640
a traditional sword.

355
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:08,474
-[sigh]

356
00:17:08,507 --> 00:17:09,174
-Rurichiyo!

357
00:17:09,207 --> 00:17:10,840
-Huh?

358
00:17:10,874 --> 00:17:12,574
-There you are.

359
00:17:12,607 --> 00:17:13,307
-What is wrong?

360
00:17:13,340 --> 00:17:15,040
You look pale.

361
00:17:15,074 --> 00:17:16,174
-It's Kenryu.

362
00:17:16,207 --> 00:17:17,640
-Did you find him?

363
00:17:17,674 --> 00:17:19,640
Where is he?

364
00:17:19,674 --> 00:17:22,074
-He says he's gonna
commit suicide.

365
00:17:27,007 --> 00:17:28,740
-Well, why should I care?

366
00:17:28,774 --> 00:17:29,774
-Wait, what?

367
00:17:29,807 --> 00:17:32,140
-Kenryu already left my service.

368
00:17:32,174 --> 00:17:34,274
His fate is none of my concern.

369
00:17:34,307 --> 00:17:38,540
-How can you even
say such a thing?

370
00:17:38,574 --> 00:17:40,507
You made him protect
you in every way,

371
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:42,574
but you won't even
consider protecting him?

372
00:17:46,340 --> 00:17:47,774
Fine, then!

373
00:17:59,674 --> 00:18:01,607
[honking]

374
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:02,107
-Huh?

375
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:05,574
[scream]

376
00:18:05,607 --> 00:18:08,040
-Are you OK?

377
00:18:08,074 --> 00:18:10,507
-Thank you, Kenryu.

378
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:12,207
Oh, Enryu.

379
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:13,040
I mean--

380
00:18:21,007 --> 00:18:24,907
-[panting]

381
00:18:29,407 --> 00:18:30,607
RURICHIYO (VOICEOVER): Kenryu!

382
00:18:35,474 --> 00:18:38,874
-Aw, you really
think this will work?

383
00:18:38,907 --> 00:18:40,607
-What are you talking about?

384
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:43,507
Wasn't this the plan you came
up with in the first place?

385
00:18:43,540 --> 00:18:47,974
-Well, yes, that's true, but--

386
00:18:48,007 --> 00:18:50,374
-Kenryu, please proceed
with your ritual.

387
00:18:50,407 --> 00:18:52,407
In fact, I will assist
you if you wish.

388
00:18:55,407 --> 00:18:56,207
-Forgive me.

389
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:58,474
I cannot go through with this.

390
00:18:58,507 --> 00:19:01,507
-Enough with the melodrama.

391
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:04,874
-I'm not being melodramatic.

392
00:19:04,907 --> 00:19:07,074
If I cannot make Lady
Rurichiyo change her mind,

393
00:19:07,107 --> 00:19:10,107
I am compelled to do whatever
it takes to stop her,

394
00:19:10,140 --> 00:19:13,174
even if that means I must do
the unthinkable and take my own

395
00:19:13,207 --> 00:19:15,007
life.

396
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:17,107
I happened upon you
all as I was wandering

397
00:19:17,140 --> 00:19:20,774
around the town trying
to build up my courage.

398
00:19:20,807 --> 00:19:23,540
-Oh, so you weren't
just there by chance.

399
00:19:23,574 --> 00:19:24,607
-I'm begging you!

400
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:25,240
Please!

401
00:19:25,274 --> 00:19:26,916
You must help me!

402
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:29,116
-Ugh.

403
00:19:29,457 --> 00:19:31,877
-Well, I still think
this is the best

404
00:19:31,877 --> 00:19:34,243
way to persuade Kenryu's master.

405
00:19:34,277 --> 00:19:35,710
-Hope you're right.

406
00:19:35,743 --> 00:19:38,110
-[gasp] She's coming!

407
00:19:38,143 --> 00:19:41,010
Quickly!

408
00:19:41,043 --> 00:19:42,043
-OK.

409
00:19:42,077 --> 00:19:43,243
-Are we ready?

410
00:19:43,277 --> 00:19:45,077
-Mm.

411
00:19:45,110 --> 00:19:45,910
[interposing voices]

412
00:20:03,110 --> 00:20:05,910
-You fool!

413
00:20:05,943 --> 00:20:06,610
-Lady Rurichiyo!

414
00:20:11,343 --> 00:20:13,043
-How could you be so brainless?

415
00:20:13,077 --> 00:20:14,443
Did you really
think going through

416
00:20:14,477 --> 00:20:16,843
with that was going
to make me happy?

417
00:20:16,877 --> 00:20:19,343
-I-- I don't know.

418
00:20:19,377 --> 00:20:21,543
-I am responsible
for my guardians,

419
00:20:21,577 --> 00:20:24,777
and that means I
cannot let you die.

420
00:20:24,810 --> 00:20:26,643
Got that?

421
00:20:26,677 --> 00:20:28,577
-You mean-- Lady Rurichiyo--

422
00:20:36,543 --> 00:20:40,010
-They certainly are a
handful, no doubt about it.

423
00:20:40,043 --> 00:20:41,777
-You're telling me.

424
00:20:41,810 --> 00:20:43,110
RURICHIYO (VOICEOVER): Oh, well.

425
00:20:43,143 --> 00:20:46,943
I suppose we will have to
concede just this once.

426
00:20:46,977 --> 00:20:50,377
-I am so happy that you
understand, my lady!

427
00:20:50,410 --> 00:20:52,210
I won't have to lose my life!

428
00:20:52,243 --> 00:20:55,843
Not for something
as dumb as kemari!

429
00:20:55,877 --> 00:20:58,043
-What did you say?

430
00:20:58,077 --> 00:20:58,843
-Uh.

431
00:20:58,877 --> 00:21:01,243
-Did you just call kemari dumb?

432
00:21:01,277 --> 00:21:04,843
So, you believe your
princess has dumb ideas?

433
00:21:04,877 --> 00:21:06,177
-No!

434
00:21:06,210 --> 00:21:09,577
I, uh, just meant-- well,
silly hobbies like kemari are--

435
00:21:09,610 --> 00:21:11,410
-What do you mean,
silly hobbies?

436
00:21:11,443 --> 00:21:13,477
-No, it-- that came out wrong.

437
00:21:13,510 --> 00:21:16,377
-I decided not to
concede the point.

438
00:21:16,410 --> 00:21:17,310
-Huh?

439
00:21:17,343 --> 00:21:19,610
But my lady, mere
seconds ago, you

440
00:21:19,643 --> 00:21:21,677
said you'd see things my way.

441
00:21:21,710 --> 00:21:25,343
-That was before you trampled
all over my feelings!

442
00:21:25,377 --> 00:21:26,743
-This is hopeless.

443
00:21:26,777 --> 00:21:29,977
-But everybody worked so hard
together to stage this in order

444
00:21:30,010 --> 00:21:31,343
to convince you that--

445
00:21:31,377 --> 00:21:32,310
-What's that?

446
00:21:32,343 --> 00:21:34,477
Staged this?

447
00:21:34,510 --> 00:21:37,277
So all this talk about
committing suicide

448
00:21:37,310 --> 00:21:38,877
was to deceive me?

449
00:21:38,910 --> 00:21:41,710
Absolutely unforgivable!

450
00:21:41,743 --> 00:21:44,977
-Well, if the cat is out
of the bag, then no kemari!

451
00:21:45,010 --> 00:21:46,977
I forbid it!

452
00:21:47,010 --> 00:21:49,810
-You do not understand, because
you have never played it!

453
00:21:49,843 --> 00:21:51,877
-Oh, I have played it plenty.

454
00:21:51,910 --> 00:21:55,577
Why, in fact, I would wager
I'm better at kemari than you,

455
00:21:55,610 --> 00:21:56,677
my lady.

456
00:21:56,710 --> 00:21:59,210
-Then I challenge you
to a kemari contest!

457
00:21:59,243 --> 00:22:00,910
That will settle this argument!

458
00:22:00,943 --> 00:22:04,210
The loser must concede the issue
and never bring it up again!

459
00:22:04,243 --> 00:22:06,243
-Fine, you have a deal!

460
00:22:06,277 --> 00:22:08,143
-How the hell did things
wind up like this?

461
00:22:16,158 --> 00:22:18,124
[theme song]

462
00:23:46,948 --> 00:23:48,548
MALE SPEAKER (VOICEOVER):
Lady Kuchiki,

463
00:23:48,582 --> 00:23:50,148
accept this small
token of goodwill

464
00:23:50,182 --> 00:23:52,115
from one noble
family to another.

465
00:23:52,148 --> 00:23:54,215
RUKIA (VOICEOVER): I'm
sorry, but I cannot.

466
00:23:54,248 --> 00:23:55,182
Wait, what?

467
00:23:55,215 --> 00:23:57,215
This is the elusive
Golden Chappy!

468
00:23:57,248 --> 00:23:59,482
MALE SPEAKER (VOICEOVER):
Getting it was no easy task.

469
00:23:59,515 --> 00:24:00,382
RUKIA (VOICEOVER): Thank you.

470
00:24:00,415 --> 00:24:00,948
OK.

471
00:24:00,982 --> 00:24:01,582
I'm listening.

472
00:24:01,615 --> 00:24:05,115
What do you want?

